
----------------------
'if' Statement:
----------------------
In JavaScript, the if statement is used for conditional execution of code. 
It allows you to execute a block of code if a specified condition is true.
          means - The if(...) statement evaluates a condition in parentheses and, if the result is true, executes a block of code. 
                 The if (â€¦) statement evaluates the expression in its parentheses and converts the result to a boolean.
--condition -- An expression that is considered to be either truthy_ or falsy.
------
syntax --
------
       if (condition) 
       {
                // Code to be executed if the condition is true
       }
       also for lingle line we can use if condition withiout this '{' '}'
--------------------------------
if...else statement
---------------------------------
 The if...else statement executes a statement if a specified condition is truthy. 
 If the condition is falsy, another statement in the optional else clause will be executed.

------
syntax --
------
       if (condition) 
        {
                    // Code to be executed if the condition is true
        } 
        else 
        {
                    // Code to be executed if the condition is false
        }
--------------------------------
 if....else if statement
---------------------------------
The if-else if-else statement in JavaScript allows us to handle multiple conditions in a more structured manner. 
It's an extension of the basic if-else statement and is useful when we have more than two possible outcomes. 
-------
syntax --
------
          if (condition1) 
          {
                     // Code to be executed if condition1 is true
          } 
          else if (condition2) 
          {
                     // Code to be executed if condition2 is true
          } 
          else if (condition3) 
          {
                    // Code to be executed if condition3 is true
          } //... we can have more else if clauses

         else {
                   // Code to be executed if none of the conditions are true
              }
--------------------------------
Nested if statements 
---------------------------------
Nested if statements in JavaScript involve placing one if statement inside another. This is done to create more complex conditions and execute different blocks of code based on multiple conditions. 
------
syntax --
------
           if (condition1)
            {
                // Code to be executed if condition1 is true

                if (condition2)
                    {
                         // Code to be executed if both condition1 and condition2 are true
                        
                    } 
                    else
                    {
                         // Code to be executed if condition1 is true but condition2 is false
                    }

            } 
            else
             {
                // Code to be executed if condition1 is false
             }

